New Records: Morocco achieved a 5-0 victory, the biggest winning margin in 2025 AFCON qualifiers.
Serhou Guirassy scored a hat-trick, the first in the 2025 qualifying matches.
Key Match Events: Guirassy scored twice in the first half and once in the second half.
Morocco's dominant performance showcased their superiority over Central African Republic.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match highlighted Morocco's strength and preparation for the AFCON.
Morocco's automatic qualification as hosts was confirmed.
Others: The match was part of the 2025 AFCON third-round qualifiers.
